</code></pre> <p>In ListView when an item goes out of screen, for efficiency ListView destroys the item and when scrolling back to that item it recreates it by calling getView() method of adapter so you have to keep an array having a boolean for the status of the button which is by default will be true as for visible and in getView() you just put a check by getting the boolean value of status from the boolean array that if true then item is visible else item is invisible. So when you disappear an item you have to set status of item also false.
I assume this is the code in your getView() and you have already defined your array of boolean with same length as items of ListView and value of true with name "yourButtonStatusBooleanArray" then following modifications will work for you.</p>
