How do I set an empty ListView's background image? <p>How yo set listview background like this.
I want to appear when the number of record 0</p>
<p><img src="https://i.stack.imgur.com/gZEyj.png" alt="enter image description here"></p> <p>There is special method in <code>ListView</code> - <a href="http://d.android.com/reference/android/widget/AdapterView.html#setEmptyView%28android.view.View%29" rel="nofollow noreferrer"><code>setEmptyView()</code></a>. You can find examples of using it <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2807253/correct-use-of-setemtpyview-in-adapterview">here</a> or <a href="http://www.littlefluffytoys.com/?p=74" rel="nofollow noreferrer">here</a>.</p>
<p><strong>Upd:</strong> second link is unavailable now. Here is quote from article:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>When you set a ListView\\\\xe2\\\\x80\\\\x99s \\\\xe2\\\\x80\\\\x9cempty view\\\\xe2\\\\x80\\\\x9d programmatically, you can end up scratching your head as to why your empty view actually doesn\\\\xe2\\\\x80\\\\x99t appear when the list is empty.<br>
If this happens, then what you forgot is that you must manually add your empty view to your view hierarchy, cos ListView won\\\\xe2\\\\x80\\\\x99t do it for you. Although it\\\\xe2\\\\x80\\\\x99s obvious when you think about it, the documentation doesn\\\\xe2\\\\x80\\\\x99t mention this detail, and Googling shows at least one person had the problem.</p>
<p>Here\\\\xe2\\\\x80\\\\x99s the code with the lines that it\\\\xe2\\\\x80\\\\x99s all too easy to forget at numbers 4 and 5\\\\xe2\\\\x80\\\\xa6 </p>
</blockquote>
<pre><code>TextView emptyView = new TextView(context);
emptyView.setLayoutParams(new LayoutParams(LayoutParams.FILL_PARENT, LayoutParams.FILL_PARENT));
emptyView.setText(\\\\xe2\\\\x80\\\\x9cThis appears when the list is empty\\\\xe2\\\\x80\\\\x9d);
emptyView.setVisibility(View.GONE);
((ViewGroup)list.getParent()).addView(emptyView);
list.setEmptyView(emptyView);
</code></pre>

